{In the final chapter on the Meran, we will cover all the miscellaneous setups available for White.} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 c6 5. e3 Nbd7 6. b3 $6 {the problem of this is that after} (6. Qc2 Be7 7. g4 $5 {White claims that we cannot take on g4 due to the threat of Rg1-Rxg7.} dxc4 8. Bxc4 (8. g5 {is too ambitious. After} Nd5 9. Bxc4 Nxc3 10. bxc3 b5 11. Bd3 Bb7 $15 {[%cal Ga7a6,Gc6c5] White has too many weaknesses in their camp.}) 8... b5 9. Be2 (9. Bd3 h6 {stopping g5.} 10. Rg1 Bb7 11. g5 hxg5 12. Nxg5 {It seems like they generate down the Kingside but after} Nd5 {[%csl Rg5,Rh2][%cal Ge7g5,Gh8h2] they are struggling.} 13. Nxd5 Bxg5 14. Nc7+ Qxc7 15. Rxg5 Rxh2 $15 {our king would be quite safe on the Kingside.}) 9... O-O {now g5 is no longer a problem as h7 isn't attacked.} 10. g5 Nd5 11. Nxd5 exd5 $1 12. Qxc6 {White wins a pawn but after} Nb6 13. Qxb5 Nc4 14. Bxc4 dxc4 $44 {[%cal Ra8h1] their light-squares are too weak.}) (6. cxd5 exd5 {[%csl Rc1] with their bishop stuck on c1, this transformation doesn't challenge us.} 7. Bd3 Bd6 {[%csl Rc1][%cal Gd6h2] bringing the bishop out to the most active square.} 8. O-O O-O 9. Qc2 Re8 {[%cal Gd7f8,Rf6e4] going for ...Nf8-Qe7-Ne4 plans.} 10. Re1 Nf8 11. h3 {it is important to prevent the light-squared bishop from being traded. Otherwise, Black would have played ...Bg4-h5-Bg6.} Qe7 $11 {[%cal Gf6e4] preparing ...Ne4.}) (6. a3 {this is just a waste of move.} Be7 7. Bd3 O-O 8. O-O b6 {we have seen this earlier.}) (6. Bd2 $5 {this has been tried by a few players. I don't see the big point though. White may play b4 in certain lines.} Be7 {we remain consistent with our setup.} 7. Bd3 O-O 8. O-O dxc4 $1 {Whenever their queen isn't on b2, we have this extra resource.} 9. Bxc4 b5 10. Bd3 (10. Be2 $5 Bb7 11. a3 {trying to fix c5 with b4 next.} (11. Rc1 a6 $15 {...c5 cannot be stopped.}) 11... a5 {this is our plan B.} 12. Qc2 Qb8 {vacating the c8-square for the other rook.} 13. Rfc1 Rc8 $11 {[%cal Gb5b4,Gc6c5] we'll play ...b4 and ...c5 next.}) 10... b4 11. Na4 Bb7 $1 {[%cal Gc6c5] an important inclusion!} ({immediate} 11... c5 {doesn't work because of} 12. dxc5 Nxc5 13. Bxb4 $1 $14 {[%cal Gb4e7,Rd1d3]}) 12. Rc1 Rc8 {[%cal Rd8a5,Gc6c5] they cannot stop ...c5 anymore.} 13. Re1 c5 14. dxc5 a5 $1 {[%csl Rc5][%cal Gd7c5] next up, ...Bxf3 or ...Nxc5!}) 6... Bb4 {[%csl Rc1] White's bishop will be misplaced.} 7. Bd2 {forced neccesity.} (7. Bb2 $2 {runs into} Ne4 8. Qc2 Qa5 9. Rc1 Qxa2 $17) 7... Qe7 8. Qc2 O-O 9. Be2 b6 $11 {[%csl Rd2][%cal Gc8b7,Gc6c5] White's bishop is misplaced. We'll play ...Bb7 & ...c5 next.} *

